First Read: 13-Jan-26
SB107 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama Board of Funeral Services; to
5 amend Sections 34-13-30.1, 34-13-191, 34-13-192, and
6 34-13-199, Code of Alabama 1975; to authorize the board to
7 impose an administrative fee on each funeral establishment for
8 each funeral arranged; to increase the initial application,
9 renewal, branch registration, and transfer fees relating to a
10 certificate of authority; to require a certificate holder to
11 file an annual statement of preneed activities conducted; to
12 require a certificate holder to file an annual report relating
13 to preneed contract activities and authorize the board to
14 require the filing of additional reports as needed; and to
15 increase the initial application and renewal fees for
16 registration as a preneed sales agent
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
18 Section 1. Sections 34-13-30.1, 34-13-191, 34-13-192,
19 and 34-13-199 of the Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read
20 as follows:
21 "§34-13-30.1
22 (a) Beginning with the 2024 fiscal year, the Department
23 of Insurance may transfer to the board quarterly, for deposit
24 by the board into the Alabama Board of Funeral Services Fund,
25 the total amount of three hundred thousand dollars ($300,000)
26 per fiscal year, to defray costs associated with the
27 administration and operation of the Alabama Preneed Funeral
28 and Cemetery Act of 2023 by the board.
Page 1

and Cemetery Act of 2023 by the board.
SB107 Enrolled
29 (b) Unless extended by an act of the Legislature, this
30 section shall be repealed at the end of the 2027 fiscal year
31 subsection (a) and this subsection shall have no further
32 effect.
33 (c) Beginning June 1, 2026, upon each final disposition
34 for which a funeral establishment makes funeral arrangements
35 or otherwise renders services regulated by this chapter, the
36 board may require each funeral establishment to pay an
37 administrative fee, not to exceed thirty dollars ($30), to the
38 board for deposit by the board into the Alabama Board of
39 Funeral Services Fund. The board, by rule, may provide
40 procedures for assessing and collecting the fee."
41 "§34-13-191
42 (a) An application to the board for a certificate of
43 authority shall be accompanied by the statement and other
44 matters described in this section in the form prescribed by
45 the board. Annually thereafter, or within an extension of time
46 therefor, as the board for good cause may grant, the person
47 authorized to engage in the sale of preneed contracts shall
48 file with the board a full and true statement of his or her
49 financial condition, transactions, and affairs, prepared on a
