126 statement of activities of the trust. Upon notice to the
127 certificate holder by the board that the certificate holder
128 has failed to file the annual statement or the statement of
129 activities of the trust, the certificate holder's authority to
130 sell preneed contracts shall cease while the default
131 continues.
132 (i) To facilitate uniformity in financial statements
133 and to facilitate analysis, the board, by rule, may adopt a
134 form for financial statements. The holder of a certificate of
135 authority may submit a written request to the board to exempt
136 the holder from filing financial statements at renewal. The
137 board may waive the requirement for filing a financial
138 statement at renewal if all of the following are satisfied:
139 (1) No valid complaint has been filed since the last
