168 "§34-13-192
Page 6

"§34-13-192
SB107 Enrolled
169 (a) On or before July 1, each Each year, the
170 certificate holder shall file a report one or more reports of
171 its preneed contract activity on a form or in a format
172 prescribed by the board and as often as deemed necessary by
173 the board. The information reported shall include the total
174 number of preneed contracts in force at the end of the
175 previous calendar year, the total number of preneed contracts
176 sold during the previous calendar year, the total number of
177 preneed contracts fulfilled during the previous calendar year,
178 the total number of preneed contracts in force at the end of
179 the previous calendar year, and such other information as may
180 be required by the board. The report shall be organized by
181 type of funding, including life insurance, annuity, trust,
182 letter of credit, or surety bond. The report shall also
183 provide a certification by the trustee of the amount of assets
184 held by the trust at the beginning of the reporting period and
185 at the end of the reporting period, together with the amount
186 of deposits and withdrawals during the reporting period. If a
187 certificate holder twice defaults in complying with the
188 requirements of this subsection, the board may require that
189 the certificate holder thereafter submit the report within 45
190 days after the end of each calendar quarter and shall continue
191 so reporting for a time to be determined by the board.
192 (b) The certificate holder shall maintain a written log
193 of preneed sales. The log shall be on a form or in a format
194 prescribed by the board, shall detail all information required
195 by the board, and shall be available for inspection at any
196 time by the board.
Page 7

time by the board.
SB107 Enrolled
197 (c) Each cemetery authority shall maintain a written
198 log of the sale of cemetery interment rights. The log shall be
199 on a form or in a format prescribed by the board and shall
200 detail all information required by the board.
201 (d) The board may maintain a statewide database of
202 preneed contracts reported to the board pursuant to subsection
203 (a). The board may make information in this database
204 searchable by the public by means of unique identifiers, or
205 any other means, that the board determines respects the
206 privacy of those involved while also protecting consumers from
207 financial waste by allowing families to determine if a
208 deceased loved one has an existing preneed contract. Any
209 preneed consumer who does not wish for his or her information
210 to appear in this searchable database may opt out by following
211 a process established by the board."
212 "§34-13-199
213 (a) All individuals who offer preneed contracts to the
214 public, or who execute preneed contracts on behalf of a
215 certificate holder, shall be registered with the board as
216 preneed sales agents, pursuant to this chapter.
217 (b) All preneed sales agents and funeral directors
218 acting as preneed sales agents shall be affiliated with the
219 certificate holder that they are representing.
220 (c) A certificate holder shall be responsible for the
221 activities of all preneed sales agents and all funeral
222 directors acting as preneed sales agents who are affiliated
223 with the certificate holder and who perform any type of
224 preneed-related activity on behalf of the certificate holder.
Page 8

preneed-related activity on behalf of the certificate holder.
SB107 Enrolled
225 In addition to the preneed sales agents and funeral directors
226 acting as preneed sales agents, each certificate holder shall
227 also be subject to discipline if its preneed sales agents or
228 funeral directors acting as preneed sales agents violate this
229 chapter.
230 (d) A preneed sales agent and a funeral director acting
231 as a preneed sales agent may sell, offer, and execute preneed
232 contracts on behalf of all properly licensed entities owned or
233 operated by the sponsoring certificate holder.
234 (e) An individual may begin operating as a preneed
235 sales agent as soon as a completed application for
236 registration, as set forth in subsection (g), is approved by
237 the board.
238 (f)(1) The qualifications for a preneed sales agent are
239 as follows:
240 a. The applicant must be at least 18 years of age.
241 b. The applicant must be in good standing with the
242 board.
243 c. The applicant may not have any felony or misdemeanor
244 convictions that relate to any activity regulated by this
245 chapter or a crime involving moral turpitude, as defined by
246 this chapter.
247 d. The applicant shall be of good moral character and
248 submit to a criminal history background check pursuant to
249 subdivision (2).
250 (2) An applicant for licensure as a preneed sales agent
251 shall submit to the board, on a form sworn to by the
252 applicant, his or her name, date of birth, Social Security
Page 9

applicant, his or her name, date of birth, Social Security
SB107 Enrolled
253 number, and two complete sets of fingerprints for completion
254 of a criminal history background check. The board shall submit
255 the fingerprints to the Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency
256 for a state criminal history background check. The
257 fingerprints shall be forwarded by the agency to the Federal
258 Bureau of Investigation for a national criminal history
259 background check. Costs associated with conducting a criminal
260 history background check shall be paid by the applicant. The
261 board shall keep information received pursuant to this
262 subdivision confidential, except that information received and
263 relied upon in denying the issuance of a certificate of
264 authority may be disclosed if necessary to support the denial.
265 All character information, including the information obtained
266 through the criminal history background checks, shall be
267 considered in licensure decisions to the extent permissible by
268 all applicable laws.
269 (g) An application for registration as a preneed sales
270 agent shall be submitted to the board with an application fee
271 determined by the board, but not to exceed thirty-three
272 dollars ($33) two hundred dollars ($200), by the certificate
273 holder in a form that has been prescribed by board rule. The
274 application shall contain, at a minimum, all of the following:
275 (1) The name, address, Social Security number, and date
276 of birth of the applicant and any other information as the
277 board may reasonably require of the applicant.
278 (2) The name, address, and license number of the
279 sponsoring certificate holder.
280 (3) A representation, signed by the applicant, that the
